1
00:00:18,940 --> 00:00:23,880
ظآزOnly after bloom comes fruitظآز

2
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:29,260
ظآزWho says glory must fade to the pastظآز

3
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,010
ظآزOnly through thunder
do you reach the cloudsظآز

4
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:43,120
ظآزWho made you the crown of every peakظآز

5
00:00:44,650 --> 00:00:47,930
ظآزI stand at the center of the stageظآز

6
00:00:47,930 --> 00:00:51,000
ظآزMy shadow is pinned against the wallظآز

7
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:56,660
ظآزFacing the light earns every medalظآز

8
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:00,880
ظآزLittle birds,
save your needless peckingظآز

9
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,160
ظآزThe open sky rises highظآز

10
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:09,830
ظآزWhen night falls,
the moon begins to shineظآز

11
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,860
ظآزI stand in the heart of these landsظآز

12
00:01:13,860 --> 00:01:17,220
ظآزMy shadow bears no crown or robeظآز

13
00:01:17,630 --> 00:01:23,300
ظآزThen I know truth needs no disguiseظآز

14
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:26,960
ظآزThe green hills see me as I amظآز

15
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,290
ظآزLike dew, lightning,
and moon on the riverظآز

16
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:34,730
ظآزShowing me exactly who I amظآز

17
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:35,980
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,980
=Episode 1=

19
00:02:07,060 --> 00:02:08,180
I'll switch with her.

20
00:02:08,180 --> 00:02:09,500
Let her marry the team leader's son.

21
00:02:10,940 --> 00:02:12,140
You're not Yi Qing'e.

22
00:02:13,540 --> 00:02:14,940
You're Mu Guiying.

23
00:02:14,940 --> 00:02:23,180
ظآزSo bitterظآز

24
00:02:23,180 --> 00:02:24,660
Her name is Yi Qin'e.

25
00:02:25,540 --> 00:02:27,500
She used to be Yi Qing'e.

26
00:02:28,020 --> 00:02:29,860
At first, she was Yi Laidi.

27
00:02:30,700 --> 00:02:32,980
Sometimes she's confused about her identity.

28
00:02:34,220 --> 00:02:35,620
From a shepherd girl in the hills,

29
00:02:35,860 --> 00:02:37,460
she became what people called

30
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:39,380
the Little Queen of Qinqiang Opera.

31
00:02:40,540 --> 00:02:41,580
Yet for half her life,

32
00:02:41,580 --> 00:02:43,420
people called her a dumb kid.

33
00:02:44,580 --> 00:02:45,660
She never knew whether that dumbness

34
00:02:46,380 --> 00:02:48,740
was a gift to her from heaven,

35
00:02:49,340 --> 00:02:50,780
or a punishment.

36
00:02:52,220 --> 00:02:53,300
Standing on the stage,

37
00:02:53,860 --> 00:02:55,460
she only wanted an answer.

38
00:02:56,460 --> 00:02:57,860
But the stage was empty.

39
00:02:58,580 --> 00:02:59,700
There was nothing on it.

40
00:03:01,060 --> 00:03:03,220
And somehow, it held everything.

41
00:03:04,540 --> 00:03:05,940
It made her think of that day.

42
00:03:06,580 --> 00:03:07,740
If her uncle hadn't

43
00:03:07,740 --> 00:03:10,180
(1976, Jiuyangou, Qinchuan Province)
come racing into Jiuyangou

44
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:11,980
on a bike,

45
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:14,780
what would her life

46
00:03:15,100 --> 00:03:16,820
have turned out to be?

47
00:03:22,740 --> 00:03:24,380
He's Hu Sanyuan,

48
00:03:24,860 --> 00:03:25,980
Laidi's uncle.

49
00:03:26,700 --> 00:03:28,820
He plays drums in the troupe.

50
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:30,540
Laidi recalled that

51
00:03:30,820 --> 00:03:32,260
she'd hardly ever seen her uncle.

52
00:03:33,220 --> 00:03:35,220
According to her mom, her uncle was

53
00:03:35,980 --> 00:03:36,820
troublesome,

54
00:03:37,220 --> 00:03:38,100
indecent,

55
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:39,140
and unreliable.

56
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:41,980
And he wouldn't settle down and marry.

57
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:43,660
He was

58
00:03:44,060 --> 00:03:45,060
a real mess.

59
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:48,620
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

60
00:03:49,180 --> 00:03:52,340
ظآزSocialism is good, so very goodظآز

61
00:03:52,820 --> 00:03:54,860
ظآزThe hostile forces are brought downظآز

62
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:58,660
ظآزThe imperialists ran off in defeatظآز

63
00:04:00,260 --> 00:04:01,580
Ladies,

64
00:04:02,140 --> 00:04:04,220
you've had the wash basins all afternoon.

65
00:04:04,220 --> 00:04:05,140
Give up this spot,

66
00:04:05,140 --> 00:04:06,500
let us guys wash up too.

67
00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:07,900
Exactly.

68
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:09,580
There's hot water by the pigpen.

69
00:04:09,580 --> 00:04:10,820
That's more your territory.

70
00:04:10,820 --> 00:04:11,740
Yeah, go over there.

71
00:04:11,740 --> 00:04:13,780
Pigs don't wash their hair, right?

72
00:04:13,780 --> 00:04:15,300
But they do get their bristles scalded.

73
00:04:15,620 --> 00:04:17,380
They're not just washing their hair.

74
00:04:17,380 --> 00:04:18,980
They're clearly trying to lure people.

75
00:04:18,980 --> 00:04:20,460
- Exactly.
- Look in the mirror.

76
00:04:20,460 --> 00:04:22,380
I'd sooner charm a pig than you.

77
00:04:22,980 --> 00:04:24,980
It's just a hair wash. Why so much talk?

78
00:04:24,980 --> 00:04:26,220
Why wash your hair at all?

79
00:04:26,220 --> 00:04:27,700
Even if you wash it bald, it won't help.

80
00:04:28,060 --> 00:04:30,380
Going bald would free up the basin.

81
00:04:32,860 --> 00:04:33,740
What are you doing?

82
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:37,300
ظآزHonghu Lakeظآز

83
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:41,340
ظآزWaves upon wavesظآز

84
00:04:41,940 --> 00:04:46,660
ظآزBy the shores of Honghuظآز

85
00:04:46,660 --> 00:04:48,100
Stop, stop. No more singing.

86
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:49,220
What are you even singing?

87
00:04:49,540 --> 00:04:50,540
What were you thinking?

88
00:04:51,100 --> 00:04:52,420
Is that really something to sing here?

89
00:04:53,020 --> 00:04:54,620
What were you thinking?

90
00:04:55,220 --> 00:04:57,540
Director, you're a performance cadre.

91
00:04:57,540 --> 00:04:59,300
Why make everything so serious?

92
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:00,460
Hua Caixiang,

93
00:05:00,940 --> 00:05:02,340
I've told you this many times.

94
00:05:03,300 --> 00:05:04,660
Everyone, pay attention.

95
00:05:05,820 --> 00:05:08,100
There's only one director in our troupe.

96
00:05:08,580 --> 00:05:11,100
You should call me Deputy Director Zhu.

97
00:05:11,660 --> 00:05:14,020
Zhu... Deputy Director Zhu.

98
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:16,420
- Pig?
- Stop it!

99
00:05:16,540 --> 00:05:17,620
Everyone, quiet down.

100
00:05:17,620 --> 00:05:18,460
I'm notifying you.

101
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:19,740
Director Huang said

102
00:05:20,260 --> 00:05:22,260
everyone, all of you, right now,

103
00:05:22,260 --> 00:05:23,860
to the rehearsal hall for a meeting.

104
00:05:23,860 --> 00:05:25,420
I haven't washed up. I'm all sweaty.

105
00:05:25,420 --> 00:05:26,260
Right now. Immediately.

106
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:32,420
How well-behaved this dog is!

107
00:05:34,980 --> 00:05:35,820
He Dachui.

108
00:05:36,540 --> 00:05:37,820
Take your dog out.

109
00:05:38,260 --> 00:05:39,940
We're in a meeting. This is improper.

110
00:05:40,660 --> 00:05:42,500
The dog heard you were speaking,

111
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:43,540
and only came to learn.

112
00:05:44,460 --> 00:05:45,540
Okay, all right. Siyuan.

113
00:05:45,940 --> 00:05:48,460
He won't let you learn. Let's go.

114
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:49,660
Siyuan.

115
00:05:51,060 --> 00:05:52,820
- You want improvement.
- Come on, go.

116
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:54,820
Don't bring the dog again.

117
00:05:54,820 --> 00:05:55,660
Got it, got it.

118
00:05:57,420 --> 00:05:58,660
Why isn't Hu Sanyuan here?

119
00:06:02,220 --> 00:06:03,060
He Dachui.

120
00:06:03,940 --> 00:06:04,940
Go get Hu Sanyuan.

121
00:06:05,780 --> 00:06:07,140
I can get Siyuan here.

122
00:06:07,140 --> 00:06:08,180
But not Sanyuan.

123
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:09,740
Quiet down.

124
00:06:10,140 --> 00:06:11,820
Who knows where Hu Sanyuan is?

125
00:06:12,260 --> 00:06:14,100
Something came up back home for him.

126
00:06:14,180 --> 00:06:15,020
He went back.

127
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:16,180
He'll be back tomorrow.

128
00:06:18,140 --> 00:06:20,420
He asked you for leave?

129
00:06:20,420 --> 00:06:21,780
Why would he?

130
00:06:21,780 --> 00:06:23,100
Who do you think I am?

131
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:24,980
I ran into him this morning.

132
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:26,380
He said he'd asked the director for leave.

133
00:06:26,380 --> 00:06:27,900
Which director? I have no idea.

134
00:06:28,900 --> 00:06:29,740
Hua Caixiang.

135
00:06:30,780 --> 00:06:31,980
What did I just tell you?

136
00:06:32,260 --> 00:06:33,100
What?

137
00:06:33,220 --> 00:06:34,060
You forgot?

138
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:36,580
Let me say this one last time.

139
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:39,580
Our troupe has only one director.

140
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:41,460
Director Huang.

141
00:06:43,980 --> 00:06:45,580
Let me make this clear too.

142
00:06:46,020 --> 00:06:47,460
The Deputy Director
of the Revolutionary Committee

143
00:06:48,220 --> 00:06:49,220
is also a director.

144
00:06:50,940 --> 00:06:52,460
As for today's meeting,

145
00:06:53,380 --> 00:06:54,500
the first item on the agenda.

146
00:06:55,820 --> 00:06:59,140
The higher-ups are coming
to inspect the work.

147
00:06:59,700 --> 00:07:02,020
The County Revolutionary Committee

148
00:07:02,020 --> 00:07:04,700
wants the troupe to perform for them.

149
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:06,660
The play has been chosen.

150
00:07:08,980 --> 00:07:09,820
Xiang Yang Hong.

151
00:07:11,380 --> 00:07:12,580
That's the piece you

152
00:07:13,860 --> 00:07:14,700
excel in.

153
00:07:15,540 --> 00:07:16,660
So annoying.

154
00:07:17,340 --> 00:07:18,180
This is your chance.

155
00:07:18,460 --> 00:07:19,300
Right?

156
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:22,340
We've done this show many times,

157
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:24,540
but we still can't let our guard down.

158
00:07:25,020 --> 00:07:26,140
This time, the audience

159
00:07:26,140 --> 00:07:28,180
isn't the usual revolutionary masses.

160
00:07:28,820 --> 00:07:30,700
This is a political assignment.

161
00:07:31,620 --> 00:07:33,660
Everyone must stay alert

162
00:07:34,580 --> 00:07:35,420
and take it seriously.

163
00:07:36,460 --> 00:07:38,460
Deputy Director Zhu and I discussed it,

164
00:07:39,180 --> 00:07:40,820
and we'll start rehearsals tomorrow.

165
00:07:41,540 --> 00:07:44,380
We must make sure it goes perfectly.

166
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:51,980
What's the next item?

167
00:07:58,660 --> 00:07:59,820
Not the next one yet.

168
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:01,540
Come on,

169
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:03,860
let's applaud this item first.

170
00:08:03,860 --> 00:08:04,700
Good.

171
00:08:04,940 --> 00:08:05,780
Good.

172
00:08:07,540 --> 00:08:08,380
Very good.

173
00:08:19,020 --> 00:08:21,060
Laidi, has your mom had the baby?

174
00:08:22,220 --> 00:08:24,060
How would I know if she gave birth?

175
00:08:24,980 --> 00:08:25,820
This kid...

176
00:08:25,980 --> 00:08:28,140
Why ask her? She's a dumb kid.

177
00:08:28,660 --> 00:08:29,540
I'm not dumb!

178
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:44,780
Some water?

179
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:46,220
Let me pour you some.

180
00:08:48,420 --> 00:08:49,780
That's my second daughter.

181
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:51,100
She's old enough to help.

182
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:54,940
Dig in.

183
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:55,820
Okay, okay.

184
00:08:55,820 --> 00:08:57,100
Come on, dig in.

185
00:09:07,540 --> 00:09:08,820
Maocai has hard luck.

186
00:09:08,820 --> 00:09:09,940
It's gotta be another girl.

187
00:09:09,940 --> 00:09:10,780
Keep it down.

188
00:09:40,780 --> 00:09:41,660
Little glutton.

189
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:44,700
My in-laws gave me a bowl of white flour.

190
00:09:44,940 --> 00:09:46,300
It's for Mom after the baby's born.

191
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:47,140
You're eating it already?

192
00:09:47,380 --> 00:09:49,100
I was just checking if it's cooked.

193
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:49,940
Liar!

194
00:09:50,660 --> 00:09:51,820
You took my hair clip again.

195
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:53,340
Stop!

196
00:10:00,060 --> 00:10:00,900
Come out.

197
00:10:01,940 --> 00:10:02,780
Give it to me.

198
00:10:04,420 --> 00:10:05,260
Give it back.

199
00:10:05,780 --> 00:10:06,780
Give it back.

200
00:10:06,780 --> 00:10:07,620
Give it back now.

201
00:10:08,180 --> 00:10:09,020
Now!

202
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:19,260
Fine, don't come out then.

203
00:10:19,420 --> 00:10:20,580
Stay hidden forever.

204
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:23,260
Try taking my stuff again.

205
00:10:23,620 --> 00:10:24,820
See if I don't beat you down.

206
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:39,180
ظآزHu Sanyuan, that Hu Sanyuanظآز

207
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:41,500
ظآزRode past ninety-nine sharp bendsظآز

208
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:43,780
ظآزNo water and no foodظآز

209
00:10:43,780 --> 00:10:46,060
ظآزNot even one deep breath to catchظآز

210
00:10:46,060 --> 00:10:48,460
ظآزHu Sanyuan, that Hu Sanyuanظآز

211
00:10:48,460 --> 00:10:50,780
ظآزRushing on till the sky grew darkظآز

212
00:10:50,780 --> 00:10:53,660
ظآزAll just for a visit back homeظآز

213
00:10:53,660 --> 00:10:55,620
ظآزA visit back homeظآز

214
00:11:09,180 --> 00:11:10,220
Where do you think you're going?

215
00:11:11,860 --> 00:11:12,780
Get some milk

216
00:11:12,860 --> 00:11:13,740
for Mom.

217
00:11:14,780 --> 00:11:15,620
Take it.

218
00:11:27,220 --> 00:11:29,380
You saw those two in the yard, right?

219
00:11:30,740 --> 00:11:32,420
If Mom has another girl,

220
00:11:33,340 --> 00:11:34,660
they'll take her away.

221
00:11:36,140 --> 00:11:36,980
Why?

222
00:11:37,660 --> 00:11:39,180
Dad can't afford another one.

223
00:11:40,540 --> 00:11:42,140
What if it's a boy?

224
00:11:45,140 --> 00:11:45,980
Then in this family,

225
00:11:46,380 --> 00:11:47,700
you'll be the extra one.

226
00:11:59,660 --> 00:12:00,580
What are you two doing?

227
00:12:00,860 --> 00:12:02,100
Why's milking taking so long?

228
00:12:02,620 --> 00:12:03,860
Now you have a baby brother.

229
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:07,140
Come back, quick.

230
00:12:22,460 --> 00:12:23,300
Maocai.

231
00:12:24,780 --> 00:12:26,660
Sanyuan? What brings you back?

232
00:12:27,180 --> 00:12:28,060
What is this?

233
00:12:28,340 --> 00:12:29,660
Go get two basins.

234
00:12:30,180 --> 00:12:31,020
Yeah, yeah.

235
00:12:34,260 --> 00:12:35,100
What is it?

236
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:36,740
Here.

237
00:12:36,740 --> 00:12:37,580
What's in it?

238
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:39,660
I brought back some white flour.

239
00:12:40,420 --> 00:12:41,580
Now it's soaked.

240
00:12:43,780 --> 00:12:44,660
What a shame!

241
00:12:45,220 --> 00:12:46,140
Well, this...

242
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:47,020
What's that?

243
00:12:47,020 --> 00:12:47,860
White sugar.

244
00:12:49,460 --> 00:12:50,740
Give it to me.

245
00:12:52,660 --> 00:12:54,180
This whole box is full of water.

246
00:12:54,980 --> 00:12:56,060
What happened?

247
00:12:56,940 --> 00:12:58,740
I had an accidental setback.

248
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:03,740
Brother, how come you're back?

249
00:13:04,460 --> 00:13:05,980
I wanted to bring you some things.

250
00:13:07,020 --> 00:13:07,860
Where's Xiuying?

251
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:09,500
She just had the baby. She's in bed.

252
00:13:10,060 --> 00:13:10,980
She did?

253
00:13:10,980 --> 00:13:11,820
What did she have?

254
00:13:11,820 --> 00:13:13,220
A boy. A boy!

255
00:13:13,740 --> 00:13:14,580
Good.

256
00:13:15,140 --> 00:13:16,060
This is wonderful news.

257
00:13:17,940 --> 00:13:19,700
Listen to that cry, so loud too.

258
00:13:19,980 --> 00:13:20,860
A healthy boy.

259
00:13:22,580 --> 00:13:23,420
Uncle.

260
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:24,980
What brings you back?

261
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:26,340
Pandi.

262
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:28,340
You've grown into a young lady.

263
00:13:29,740 --> 00:13:30,580
That's great.

264
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:32,340
Want to learn opera?

265
00:13:32,740 --> 00:13:34,260
Where would I learn it?

266
00:13:34,420 --> 00:13:35,260
At the county troupe.

267
00:13:35,820 --> 00:13:36,660
What do you mean?

268
00:13:36,780 --> 00:13:38,540
To train fresh talent,

269
00:13:39,540 --> 00:13:40,500
the troupe has decided

270
00:13:40,860 --> 00:13:42,020
to open recruitment

271
00:13:42,540 --> 00:13:43,900
for a group of new trainees.

272
00:13:45,780 --> 00:13:46,780
It is

273
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:49,540
the first time in ten years our troupe

274
00:13:49,540 --> 00:13:51,020
is taking in recruits.

275
00:13:51,940 --> 00:13:53,420
As far as I know,

276
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,940
some people have started making moves.

277
00:13:57,620 --> 00:14:01,380
Pulling strings for friends

278
00:14:02,180 --> 00:14:03,180
and family.

279
00:14:03,700 --> 00:14:05,620
The county troupe's hiring junior trainees.

280
00:14:07,140 --> 00:14:08,060
If you get into

281
00:14:08,980 --> 00:14:11,140
the troupe, you'll get
state-supplied grain.

282
00:14:12,020 --> 00:14:13,420
This only happens once in decades.

283
00:14:13,940 --> 00:14:15,260
It's a once-in-a-lifetime chance.

284
00:14:15,620 --> 00:14:18,380
Then can our Pandi make it or not?

285
00:14:18,380 --> 00:14:19,380
Why wouldn't she?

286
00:14:19,380 --> 00:14:20,220
You've got me.

287
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:21,780
I know you're the lead percussionist.

288
00:14:21,780 --> 00:14:23,100
But you're not one of the troupe leaders.

289
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:24,260
Can you really make it happen?

290
00:14:24,260 --> 00:14:25,140
What do you know?

291
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:26,140
A lead percussionist is

292
00:14:27,060 --> 00:14:28,620
the soul of the whole performance.

293
00:14:31,140 --> 00:14:32,340
Shameful!

294
00:14:36,140 --> 00:14:37,900
Our troupe is a revolutionary troupe.

295
00:14:38,780 --> 00:14:40,660
Not a private troupe from the old society.

296
00:14:41,860 --> 00:14:43,620
Don't bring those bad practices here.

297
00:14:44,820 --> 00:14:46,340
The troupe's Revolutionary Committee

298
00:14:46,900 --> 00:14:48,500
has decided on two rules.

299
00:14:49,740 --> 00:14:50,580
First,

300
00:14:51,460 --> 00:14:53,300
we must keep strict political screening.

301
00:14:53,580 --> 00:14:55,100
To keep the revolutionary ranks clean,

302
00:14:55,700 --> 00:14:59,140
we'd rather take rough talent
from poor peasants

303
00:14:59,140 --> 00:15:02,060
than picks from landlords
and rich peasants.

304
00:15:02,780 --> 00:15:03,940
Director, I don't quite get it.

305
00:15:04,420 --> 00:15:06,340
Are we taking rough talent or picks?

306
00:15:06,660 --> 00:15:09,180
We pick the best among the rough talent.

307
00:15:09,180 --> 00:15:10,100
Best picks.

308
00:15:11,220 --> 00:15:12,980
You really are capable.

309
00:15:12,980 --> 00:15:14,340
You still don't get it.

310
00:15:14,940 --> 00:15:15,860
After the meeting ends,

311
00:15:15,860 --> 00:15:16,900
come to my office.

312
00:15:19,700 --> 00:15:20,540
Early tomorrow morning,

313
00:15:20,980 --> 00:15:21,900
I'll take Pandi with me.

314
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:25,180
We need a note from the production team.

315
00:15:25,180 --> 00:15:26,100
That's easy.

316
00:15:26,460 --> 00:15:27,940
Her father-in-law is the team leader.

317
00:15:27,940 --> 00:15:28,900
He can approve as many as we need.

318
00:15:29,180 --> 00:15:31,100
Quick, go tell your father-in-law.

319
00:15:31,420 --> 00:15:32,260
And bring the drinks.

320
00:15:32,980 --> 00:15:33,820
Okay.

321
00:15:34,060 --> 00:15:34,900
Brother,

322
00:15:34,980 --> 00:15:36,860
our family's got a double celebration.

323
00:15:37,140 --> 00:15:38,300
She's already engaged?

324
00:15:39,460 --> 00:15:42,060
She got engaged to the team leader's son.

325
00:15:43,700 --> 00:15:44,900
She is still so young.

326
00:15:45,340 --> 00:15:50,140
ظآزSing a folk song for the Partyظآز

327
00:15:50,260 --> 00:15:54,340
ظآزI see the Party like a motherظآز

328
00:15:54,340 --> 00:15:55,780
Sis, where are you going?

329
00:15:55,780 --> 00:15:56,940
Get back to your work.

330
00:15:57,540 --> 00:16:00,860
ظآزMy heart's lit upظآز

331
00:16:11,060 --> 00:16:11,900
Have a seat.

332
00:16:20,700 --> 00:16:21,820
Someone reported that

333
00:16:21,820 --> 00:16:23,380
you and certain people

334
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:24,860
had an improper relationship.

335
00:16:25,460 --> 00:16:26,540
With whom?

336
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:28,740
Hu Sanyuan.

337
00:16:29,420 --> 00:16:31,140
It is not just one person saying it.

338
00:16:31,740 --> 00:16:33,220
They say that

339
00:16:33,220 --> 00:16:34,580
your looks are suggestive,

340
00:16:34,580 --> 00:16:36,060
your behavior crosses the line,

341
00:16:36,060 --> 00:16:37,940
and the way you talk is too direct.

342
00:16:37,940 --> 00:16:39,620
That is made up, plain slander.

343
00:16:40,540 --> 00:16:42,420
Hu and I have always been like this.

344
00:16:42,420 --> 00:16:44,540
He's the band drummer.
I'm the lead performer.

345
00:16:44,540 --> 00:16:46,060
The nature of our work

346
00:16:46,060 --> 00:16:49,060
means we talk a lot on and offstage.

347
00:16:49,700 --> 00:16:50,540
I know.

348
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:52,100
People are jealous, that is all.

349
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:54,540
Well,

350
00:16:55,260 --> 00:16:56,620
about this, hear me out.

351
00:16:57,340 --> 00:16:59,060
Your spouse and I

352
00:16:59,060 --> 00:17:00,900
are both leading cadres at work.

353
00:17:01,540 --> 00:17:03,940
He is away all year.

354
00:17:03,940 --> 00:17:05,500
As your supervisor,

355
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:08,900
I should look out for you for him.

356
00:17:09,340 --> 00:17:10,660
I thank you for him.

357
00:17:11,580 --> 00:17:12,940
I'll write to him.

358
00:17:13,260 --> 00:17:14,820
I'll tell him about your kindness to me,

359
00:17:14,820 --> 00:17:17,300
and about the pure revolutionary friendship

360
00:17:17,300 --> 00:17:19,100
of Comrade Hu Sanyuan and me.

361
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:22,380
Come on, Sanyuan, eat up.

362
00:17:23,380 --> 00:17:25,340
You came all this way,
over hills and ridges,

363
00:17:25,340 --> 00:17:26,700
just to get here to Jiuyangou.

364
00:17:27,060 --> 00:17:28,260
Our production team welcomes you.

365
00:17:28,940 --> 00:17:30,420
Over hills and ridges?

366
00:17:31,340 --> 00:17:32,540
No need to be so polite.

367
00:17:34,820 --> 00:17:35,860
We're way out in the middle of nowhere.

368
00:17:35,860 --> 00:17:36,820
We don't have much to offer you.

369
00:17:37,460 --> 00:17:38,300
It's a bit modest.

370
00:17:38,780 --> 00:17:39,620
I hope you'll understand.

371
00:17:39,620 --> 00:17:41,420
Why be polite? We're family here.

372
00:17:42,260 --> 00:17:43,460
Do you know what kind of bond we have?

373
00:17:43,940 --> 00:17:44,780
I do.

374
00:17:45,740 --> 00:17:46,700
We're all one family.

375
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:47,780
So let's not talk like strangers.

376
00:17:49,100 --> 00:17:51,220
You think that kid can get into the troupe?

377
00:17:52,100 --> 00:17:54,260
Ask around for miles and miles.

378
00:17:54,260 --> 00:17:56,460
When Sanyuan plays the drum,

379
00:17:56,460 --> 00:17:57,820
if he's second, no one's first.

380
00:17:58,100 --> 00:17:59,820
Sanyuan has the final say on this.

381
00:18:00,260 --> 00:18:01,260
Does he?

382
00:18:01,980 --> 00:18:03,260
We asked him to buy chemical fertilizer,

383
00:18:03,460 --> 00:18:04,300
and he agreed.

384
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:05,780
In the end, he hauled back manure.

385
00:18:05,780 --> 00:18:06,660
What do you say?

386
00:18:07,220 --> 00:18:08,340
That's different.

387
00:18:08,340 --> 00:18:10,140
The troupe doesn't make
chemical fertilizer.

388
00:18:10,140 --> 00:18:11,900
Training in opera is not the same thing.

389
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:12,740
Right, right.

390
00:18:13,420 --> 00:18:14,260
Sanyuan.

391
00:18:14,620 --> 00:18:17,100
Honestly, can the kid join the troupe?

392
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:17,940
You get the final say?

393
00:18:21,220 --> 00:18:22,580
What to plant this year?

394
00:18:22,860 --> 00:18:24,460
Corn or potatoes, you decide that?

395
00:18:24,460 --> 00:18:25,420
Of course. I'm the team leader.

396
00:18:25,660 --> 00:18:26,620
I'm the examiner.

397
00:18:28,140 --> 00:18:28,980
I get it.

398
00:18:32,380 --> 00:18:34,380
The certificate. Is this okay?

399
00:18:34,820 --> 00:18:35,820
As long as it proves

400
00:18:35,820 --> 00:18:37,260
the kid is from a peasant family.

401
00:18:37,260 --> 00:18:38,740
Just take a look.

402
00:18:38,740 --> 00:18:39,580
No need.

403
00:18:39,820 --> 00:18:40,660
Well, um...

404
00:18:40,660 --> 00:18:41,620
I'll read it to you.

405
00:18:41,620 --> 00:18:42,660
I'll read it out.

406
00:18:42,660 --> 00:18:43,500
Well...

407
00:18:44,260 --> 00:18:45,100
Fine.

408
00:18:45,100 --> 00:18:45,940
Go on, read it.

409
00:18:46,140 --> 00:18:48,580
To the leaders of
the Troupe Revolutionary Committee.

410
00:18:48,580 --> 00:18:50,980
We heard the troupe is recruiting
junior trainees,

411
00:18:51,580 --> 00:18:54,260
so we recommend Gao Wufu

412
00:18:54,260 --> 00:18:57,420
and Yi Pandi for the exam.

413
00:18:57,780 --> 00:18:59,220
Gao Wufu and Yi Pandi are

414
00:18:59,220 --> 00:19:00,060
both from...

415
00:19:00,060 --> 00:19:00,900
Wait, wait.

416
00:19:01,740 --> 00:19:02,700
Who is Gao Wufu?

417
00:19:04,420 --> 00:19:05,260
It's him.

418
00:19:05,580 --> 00:19:06,500
Your niece's husband.

419
00:19:08,220 --> 00:19:09,340
Don't be ridiculous.

420
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:10,780
How is this ridiculous?

421
00:19:11,380 --> 00:19:12,220
This won't work.

422
00:19:12,220 --> 00:19:14,220
We're all family. They're a young couple.

423
00:19:14,220 --> 00:19:15,100
Why wouldn't it work?

424
00:19:15,100 --> 00:19:15,940
No way.

425
00:19:16,340 --> 00:19:17,820
Why not? You're the examiner.

426
00:19:17,820 --> 00:19:18,660
You make the call.

427
00:19:19,100 --> 00:19:20,180
Only one can go.

428
00:19:22,620 --> 00:19:23,500
Then neither of them is going.

429
00:19:25,780 --> 00:19:26,860
Your daughter-in-law

430
00:19:27,340 --> 00:19:28,780
gets to move to the city

431
00:19:28,780 --> 00:19:30,100
and live on state-supplied grain.

432
00:19:30,740 --> 00:19:33,100
If your niece leaves
for state-supplied grain,

433
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:33,980
do you think she'll come back?

434
00:19:34,260 --> 00:19:35,700
When she finally leaves,

435
00:19:35,700 --> 00:19:36,740
why would she come back?

436
00:19:36,740 --> 00:19:37,900
Then what about my son?

437
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:38,940
When they get married,

438
00:19:38,940 --> 00:19:40,300
they'll move to the city together.

439
00:19:40,700 --> 00:19:42,460
The troupe is full of pretty faces.

440
00:19:42,460 --> 00:19:43,820
Seeing white steamed buns every day,

441
00:19:43,820 --> 00:19:44,660
if it were your kid,

442
00:19:44,660 --> 00:19:46,140
could they still eat cornmeal steamed buns?

443
00:19:46,140 --> 00:19:47,220
No way.

444
00:19:47,220 --> 00:19:48,500
They've had an engagement since childhood.

445
00:19:48,940 --> 00:19:50,420
If she wants to abandon her husband,

446
00:19:50,420 --> 00:19:51,500
then as her father,

447
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:52,580
I'll be the first to say no.

448
00:19:52,580 --> 00:19:54,060
You expect me to buy that?

449
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:56,140
Sir,

450
00:19:56,340 --> 00:19:58,220
this affects a kid's whole future.

451
00:19:58,220 --> 00:19:59,500
You can't look at it that way.

452
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:00,660
You're wrong again.

453
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:02,620
It's two kids' futures.

454
00:20:02,620 --> 00:20:04,380
So my kid's future doesn't count?

455
00:20:05,540 --> 00:20:06,580
As the team leader,

456
00:20:06,580 --> 00:20:08,100
you can't be this selfish.

457
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:10,060
Fine, I'm done talking.

458
00:20:10,580 --> 00:20:11,700
No certificate. I'm not doing it.

459
00:20:13,620 --> 00:20:14,940
You're stupid!

460
00:20:15,140 --> 00:20:15,980
You...

461
00:20:15,980 --> 00:20:16,860
You are cursing me?

462
00:20:16,860 --> 00:20:17,820
I am cursing you!

463
00:20:17,820 --> 00:20:18,700
You drummer.

464
00:20:18,700 --> 00:20:19,580
You came to our Jiuyangou

465
00:20:19,580 --> 00:20:20,420
to show off?

466
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:21,660
What's your problem?

467
00:20:21,660 --> 00:20:23,460
No, he... He didn't mean it.

468
00:20:23,460 --> 00:20:24,860
Whatever it is, let's talk it out.

469
00:20:24,860 --> 00:20:25,820
Save it!

470
00:20:26,420 --> 00:20:27,260
I'm telling you,

471
00:20:27,700 --> 00:20:29,340
any kid can go except Pandi.

472
00:21:24,660 --> 00:21:25,580
Sanyuan,

473
00:21:26,100 --> 00:21:28,220
think of another way for them.

474
00:21:28,580 --> 00:21:30,660
You all act like I run the troupe.

475
00:21:30,660 --> 00:21:32,940
Like I can let in whoever I want.

476
00:21:38,140 --> 00:21:39,380
What are you doing? Let go!

477
00:21:39,380 --> 00:21:40,260
Come with me.

478
00:21:41,540 --> 00:21:42,620
Let go!

479
00:21:45,260 --> 00:21:46,100
Dad.

480
00:21:46,620 --> 00:21:47,740
I'll switch with her.

481
00:21:47,740 --> 00:21:49,060
Let her marry the team leader's son.

482
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:50,540
She's better at work than I am.

483
00:21:50,540 --> 00:21:51,380
Look, look.

484
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:53,340
She hasn't even trained in opera!

485
00:21:54,340 --> 00:21:55,180
Nonsense!

486
00:21:55,380 --> 00:21:56,620
You think we can just swap people?

487
00:21:56,620 --> 00:21:58,340
I don't care. I want to perform opera.

488
00:21:58,340 --> 00:21:59,340
Shut up!

489
00:22:06,940 --> 00:22:07,780
Who's she?

490
00:22:09,500 --> 00:22:10,860
Well... Laidi.

491
00:22:12,460 --> 00:22:13,940
How'd the kid end up like a beggar?

492
00:22:13,940 --> 00:22:14,980
I didn't recognize her.

493
00:22:15,940 --> 00:22:16,860
She's out herding sheep all day,

494
00:22:17,180 --> 00:22:18,780
now she looks like one herself.

495
00:22:20,580 --> 00:22:22,060
Take her with you.

496
00:22:22,660 --> 00:22:23,700
I'll get the certificate.

497
00:22:24,980 --> 00:22:25,820
Dad.

498
00:22:26,020 --> 00:22:26,860
Dad...

499
00:22:53,660 --> 00:22:54,500
Brother.

500
00:23:09,420 --> 00:23:10,420
I'll try

501
00:23:10,420 --> 00:23:12,780
to get the kid into the troupe.

502
00:23:17,180 --> 00:23:19,180
If not, don't send her back either.

503
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:21,340
Just let her stay in the city.

504
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:22,900
Any job is fine.

505
00:23:44,180 --> 00:23:45,260
Why are you crying?

506
00:23:45,620 --> 00:23:47,620
Dad doesn't want me anymore.

507
00:23:47,620 --> 00:23:48,980
You dumb kid.

508
00:23:50,460 --> 00:23:51,700
How are you this lucky?

509
00:23:52,780 --> 00:23:54,060
I'm not going anywhere.

510
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:55,700
I want to go.

511
00:23:57,740 --> 00:23:59,300
I want to go.

512
00:24:04,340 --> 00:24:06,340
I want to go.

513
00:24:59,300 --> 00:25:00,140
Alright.

514
00:25:01,020 --> 00:25:01,860
Stop here.

515
00:25:03,220 --> 00:25:04,500
Alright, let the kid come with me.

516
00:25:05,220 --> 00:25:06,060
Mom.

517
00:25:06,060 --> 00:25:06,900
Laidi.

518
00:25:07,420 --> 00:25:08,340
You should get going.

519
00:25:10,500 --> 00:25:11,380
Your uncle is waiting.

520
00:25:11,380 --> 00:25:12,220
Go.

521
00:25:14,620 --> 00:25:15,460
Go.

522
00:25:18,820 --> 00:25:19,660
Mom.

523
00:25:41,140 --> 00:25:42,060
Hold your uncle.

524
00:25:48,300 --> 00:25:49,140
Come.

525
00:25:49,140 --> 00:25:50,260
No.

526
00:26:07,900 --> 00:26:13,460
ظآزAcross the hills it bloomsظآز

527
00:26:14,940 --> 00:26:18,460
ظآزAzalea blossomsظآز

528
00:26:22,260 --> 00:26:24,100
Ms. Hua, off to rehearsal?

529
00:26:24,980 --> 00:26:26,860
The leaders are coming
to watch Xiang Yang Hong.

530
00:26:28,940 --> 00:26:30,980
You've done this play hundreds of times.

531
00:26:30,980 --> 00:26:32,180
You still need rehearsal?

532
00:26:32,180 --> 00:26:34,820
I do, or I'll get rusty.

533
00:26:36,740 --> 00:26:38,460
Your man hasn't come back

534
00:26:38,980 --> 00:26:40,500
for half a year, right?

535
00:26:41,180 --> 00:26:42,140
You haven't been idle.

536
00:26:42,140 --> 00:26:43,580
You're even counting the days.

537
00:26:43,580 --> 00:26:45,300
What, you got your eye on him?

538
00:26:45,300 --> 00:26:46,140
Waiting for him?

539
00:26:47,300 --> 00:26:48,820
No way, I wouldn't aim that high.

540
00:26:53,140 --> 00:26:55,980
ظآزThe Great Leap red flagظآز

541
00:27:00,860 --> 00:27:03,460
ظآزIs waving in the windظآز

542
00:27:16,300 --> 00:27:17,140
Ms. Hua.

543
00:27:17,900 --> 00:27:19,580
You weren't here yet, so I practiced.

544
00:27:20,140 --> 00:27:21,580
Go on, keep practicing.

545
00:27:22,300 --> 00:27:24,060
I wouldn't dare show off here.

546
00:27:24,340 --> 00:27:25,580
You practice. I'll learn from you.

547
00:27:27,260 --> 00:27:28,740
Mi Lan knows that it's pointless

548
00:27:29,340 --> 00:27:30,660
to practice.

549
00:27:31,340 --> 00:27:33,700
There's only one show for the leaders.

550
00:27:33,700 --> 00:27:36,380
An understudy never gets onstage.

551
00:27:36,380 --> 00:27:37,620
That's not always true.

552
00:27:37,620 --> 00:27:38,900
What if I have diarrhoea?

553
00:27:40,060 --> 00:27:42,580
Or lose my voice, or break a leg.

554
00:27:42,580 --> 00:27:44,660
Enough. What nonsense are you saying?

555
00:27:44,660 --> 00:27:45,860
Not a chance, Ms. Hua.

556
00:27:46,300 --> 00:27:47,900
Not even one in ten thousand.

557
00:27:47,900 --> 00:27:49,660
Yeah, Mi Lan's right.

558
00:27:50,140 --> 00:27:51,060
All these years,

559
00:27:51,060 --> 00:27:52,420
have you ever seen her get one shot?

560
00:27:52,420 --> 00:27:53,260
I'm the same.

561
00:27:53,260 --> 00:27:55,460
I never got one shot with Hu Sanyuan.

562
00:27:55,740 --> 00:27:56,820
If you want this kind of job,

563
00:27:56,820 --> 00:27:58,020
you need the real skills for it.

564
00:27:58,580 --> 00:28:00,420
But you only trust Hu Sanyuan's skills.

565
00:28:00,740 --> 00:28:02,420
What can I do, right?

566
00:28:02,420 --> 00:28:04,420
You're already in the seat, aren't you?

567
00:28:04,940 --> 00:28:06,500
Then grab the chance.

568
00:28:06,500 --> 00:28:07,340
Okay.

569
00:28:07,820 --> 00:28:08,860
Let us

570
00:28:09,580 --> 00:28:11,260
back up the lead role for once. Come on.

571
00:28:12,340 --> 00:28:13,180
Where to start?

572
00:28:13,540 --> 00:28:16,300
He Dachui, start with Kuyin, two-six.

573
00:28:18,020 --> 00:28:18,860
Two-six?

574
00:28:18,980 --> 00:28:19,820
Right.

575
00:28:20,060 --> 00:28:24,620
ظآزI step outside,
feeling my back pull behindظآز

576
00:28:24,620 --> 00:28:28,740
ظآزSo the belly stays out in frontظآز

577
00:28:29,260 --> 00:28:33,620
ظآزHis first uncle and second uncle
are both his unclesظآز

578
00:28:33,620 --> 00:28:37,820
ظآزTall tables, low stools, all woodظآز

579
00:28:37,820 --> 00:28:42,180
ظآزOne step forward, one back, no gainظآز

580
00:28:42,700 --> 00:28:43,580
Sounds good, right?

581
00:28:45,580 --> 00:28:47,380
If I had learned to perform opera,

582
00:28:47,380 --> 00:28:48,820
I'd be great at it.

583
00:28:50,140 --> 00:28:52,620
But I just liked drums.

584
00:28:53,220 --> 00:28:54,100
Know why that was?

585
00:28:54,900 --> 00:28:57,940
If you perform opera, you play one role.

586
00:28:58,580 --> 00:29:01,740
But on drums, you back every role.

587
00:29:02,740 --> 00:29:04,180
Sheng, Dan, Jing, and Chou.

588
00:29:04,180 --> 00:29:05,580
It's like you've played them all.

589
00:29:06,420 --> 00:29:08,220
You won't get it now.

590
00:29:08,820 --> 00:29:10,140
When you're older, you'll understand.

591
00:29:14,140 --> 00:29:14,980
Can you sing?

592
00:29:15,300 --> 00:29:16,340
Sing a song for me.

593
00:29:18,500 --> 00:29:19,340
Say something.

594
00:29:19,700 --> 00:29:21,100
Why's this kid so quiet?

595
00:29:22,180 --> 00:29:26,940
ظآزHis first uncle and second uncle
are both his unclesظآز

596
00:29:29,740 --> 00:29:30,580
This kid...

597
00:29:32,100 --> 00:29:32,940
Laidi.

598
00:29:35,660 --> 00:29:36,500
Laidi.

599
00:29:36,500 --> 00:29:40,100
ظآزEven lumps of gold and silver
are still not enoughظآز

600
00:29:40,100 --> 00:29:40,940
Laidi.

601
00:29:44,140 --> 00:29:44,980
Laidi.

602
00:29:47,180 --> 00:29:50,180
ظآزKid, don't get carried awayظآز

603
00:29:54,580 --> 00:29:55,420
Laidi.

604
00:30:23,940 --> 00:30:25,100
Why were you running?

605
00:30:26,540 --> 00:30:27,380
Running away?

606
00:30:27,940 --> 00:30:29,420
You really don't know what's good.

607
00:30:30,580 --> 00:30:31,980
Are you meant to herd sheep or what?

608
00:30:32,260 --> 00:30:33,620
I crossed all those hills,

609
00:30:34,020 --> 00:30:35,620
just to find a dumb kid like you.

610
00:30:36,260 --> 00:30:37,540
Go on. Get back. Run.

611
00:30:38,100 --> 00:30:39,740
If I chase you again, I'm a mutt.

612
00:30:41,020 --> 00:30:41,860
Where are you going?

613
00:30:45,180 --> 00:30:46,420
What a dumb kid.

614
00:30:49,860 --> 00:30:50,980
What are you looking for there?

615
00:30:54,940 --> 00:30:55,780
What are you doing?

616
00:31:14,940 --> 00:31:15,780
Alright, alright.

617
00:31:27,580 --> 00:31:29,460
We're done. The bike is wrecked.

618
00:31:30,620 --> 00:31:31,580
My military trousers...

619
00:31:32,180 --> 00:31:34,340
I worked so hard to get them.

620
00:31:34,340 --> 00:31:35,580
You couldn't just buy them.

621
00:31:36,420 --> 00:31:37,420
Now they're ruined too.

622
00:31:37,700 --> 00:31:39,100
All because you kept running.

623
00:31:40,580 --> 00:31:41,820
Think this through right now.

624
00:31:42,300 --> 00:31:43,300
Are you heading back,

625
00:31:43,300 --> 00:31:44,260
or are you coming with me?

626
00:31:45,060 --> 00:31:46,140
If you come with me,

627
00:31:46,460 --> 00:31:47,540
there's no turning back.

628
00:31:49,260 --> 00:31:52,620
ظآزCould someone be scheming in secretظآز

629
00:31:52,620 --> 00:31:53,540
Stop, stop, stop.

630
00:31:54,540 --> 00:31:55,380
What is it?

631
00:31:56,140 --> 00:31:56,980
What is it?

632
00:31:57,820 --> 00:31:58,660
Too slow.

633
00:31:58,980 --> 00:32:00,700
Can't you feel that yourself?

634
00:32:01,060 --> 00:32:02,820
Can you keep the rhythm better?

635
00:32:03,340 --> 00:32:04,220
Alright, alright.

636
00:32:05,100 --> 00:32:06,420
Pick it up. Faster, faster.

637
00:32:06,420 --> 00:32:07,580
- One more time.
- Okay.

638
00:32:07,580 --> 00:32:08,620
What a mess-up.

639
00:32:09,020 --> 00:32:09,900
- Come on, faster.
- Okay.

640
00:32:11,220 --> 00:32:12,060
Go.

641
00:32:16,380 --> 00:32:22,620
ظآزWhat's before me feels like a mazeظآز

642
00:32:23,740 --> 00:32:29,700
ظآزI'm upset and anxious beyond wordsظآز

643
00:32:29,700 --> 00:32:35,020
ظآزCould someone be scheming in secretظآز

644
00:32:35,020 --> 00:32:37,700
ظآزCould the commune members suspectظآز

645
00:32:37,700 --> 00:32:40,820
ظآزCould Father mean to step asideظآز

646
00:32:40,820 --> 00:32:43,140
ظآزOr am I too weak for this weightظآز

647
00:32:43,140 --> 00:32:48,180
ظآزI scan the road, but no one's thereظآز

648
00:32:48,180 --> 00:32:53,460
ظآزIn the hazy moonlight, not a soulظآز

649
00:32:57,860 --> 00:32:59,220
What? Still too slow?

650
00:32:59,580 --> 00:33:00,620
Too fast.

651
00:33:01,140 --> 00:33:02,620
Are you doing it on purpose?

652
00:33:02,620 --> 00:33:04,300
Or you really can't find the beat?

653
00:33:04,300 --> 00:33:05,380
Too fast now?

654
00:33:05,380 --> 00:33:06,260
He Dachui.

655
00:33:06,260 --> 00:33:08,340
Can you stop pounding blindly?

656
00:33:08,340 --> 00:33:10,100
Watch her moves, okay?

657
00:33:10,100 --> 00:33:11,740
I should focus on the drum, okay?

658
00:33:12,100 --> 00:33:13,220
At least you've got to

659
00:33:13,220 --> 00:33:14,820
leave me some room.

660
00:33:15,220 --> 00:33:16,140
You're really hard to please.

661
00:33:16,140 --> 00:33:17,820
Yeah, yeah, got it, got it.

662
00:33:18,020 --> 00:33:19,940
Speed up when needed, slow down too.

663
00:33:20,500 --> 00:33:21,940
Right, right, right.

664
00:33:39,620 --> 00:33:40,500
Where's Qin Bawa?

665
00:33:40,500 --> 00:33:41,940
He went out.

666
00:33:43,300 --> 00:33:44,260
Where to?

667
00:33:44,860 --> 00:33:46,540
Have a seat. He'll be back soon.

668
00:33:53,380 --> 00:33:54,220
Have some water.

669
00:33:56,220 --> 00:33:57,060
Sit.

670
00:34:02,100 --> 00:34:03,260
Where'd he go?

671
00:34:03,740 --> 00:34:08,580
ظآزCould someone be scheming in secretظآز

672
00:34:16,940 --> 00:34:17,820
What is it?

673
00:34:17,820 --> 00:34:19,100
Was it too fast or too slow?

674
00:34:19,100 --> 00:34:20,020
Neither fast nor slow.

675
00:34:20,460 --> 00:34:21,300
Then what's the problem?

676
00:34:21,380 --> 00:34:23,340
It was too soft.

677
00:34:23,340 --> 00:34:24,180
Soft?

678
00:34:24,500 --> 00:34:25,660
Check this power!

679
00:34:26,180 --> 00:34:27,700
How it feels to you, I don't know.

680
00:34:29,900 --> 00:34:30,940
What are you laughing at?

681
00:34:32,460 --> 00:34:34,260
Hu Sanyuan played it like this too.

682
00:34:34,460 --> 00:34:35,940
Not even close.

683
00:34:36,500 --> 00:34:39,540
Hu Sanyuan knew when to go light,

684
00:34:39,860 --> 00:34:40,820
and when to go hard.

685
00:34:40,820 --> 00:34:42,940
It all follows the character's mind.

686
00:34:42,940 --> 00:34:45,660
Every beat gave me chills inside.

687
00:34:45,660 --> 00:34:47,460
It made me want to sing out loud.

688
00:34:48,140 --> 00:34:49,820
What? Hu Sanyuan gave you

689
00:34:49,820 --> 00:34:51,180
chills inside?

690
00:34:52,420 --> 00:34:54,260
Was that beating a drum or a person?

691
00:34:55,700 --> 00:34:56,580
Exactly.

692
00:34:57,260 --> 00:34:58,340
I'm playing a person.

693
00:34:58,340 --> 00:34:59,940
The words are spoken, the feelings sung.

694
00:35:00,340 --> 00:35:02,180
When you strike the drum,
you strike the soul.

695
00:35:02,900 --> 00:35:04,380
You know what I've noticed about you?

696
00:35:04,380 --> 00:35:05,380
Who's the leading actress?

697
00:35:05,740 --> 00:35:06,660
Who's the leading actress?

698
00:35:06,660 --> 00:35:08,100
I am. What is it?

699
00:35:08,660 --> 00:35:09,860
You little troublemaker.

700
00:35:10,700 --> 00:35:11,540
This woman.

701
00:35:11,620 --> 00:35:13,260
She went after a revolutionary cadre.

702
00:35:13,900 --> 00:35:14,900
Went after?

703
00:35:14,900 --> 00:35:16,140
Me? Who did I go after?

704
00:35:16,140 --> 00:35:17,020
My man.

705
00:35:17,020 --> 00:35:18,220
Your man? Who is that?

706
00:35:18,620 --> 00:35:19,900
You're still putting on a show here?

707
00:35:20,340 --> 00:35:22,260
That letter of accusation hit my home.

708
00:35:22,540 --> 00:35:24,460
I'm going to teach you a lesson today.

709
00:35:24,460 --> 00:35:25,300
What are you doing?

710
00:35:26,500 --> 00:35:28,380
What is this mess? Stop it now.

711
00:35:28,380 --> 00:35:29,220
Pull her away.

712
00:35:30,380 --> 00:35:31,380
He Dachui, get her out of here.

713
00:35:31,780 --> 00:35:32,620
- Zhang Yinwa!
- Stop it.

714
00:35:32,620 --> 00:35:33,620
Who is your man?

715
00:35:33,620 --> 00:35:34,620
Why are you making a scene here?

716
00:35:35,540 --> 00:35:37,500
No wonder you kept me from the troupe.

717
00:35:37,500 --> 00:35:39,340
So that homewrecker lured you in?

718
00:35:39,340 --> 00:35:40,740
I'll deal with her today.

719
00:35:40,980 --> 00:35:42,420
- What are you doing?
- I told you!

720
00:35:42,420 --> 00:35:43,260
Calm down!

721
00:35:43,260 --> 00:35:44,100
I will get to the bottom of

722
00:35:44,100 --> 00:35:45,140
the letter of accusation!

723
00:35:45,140 --> 00:35:45,980
Let go of me.

724
00:35:45,980 --> 00:35:46,900
Listen to me, everyone.

725
00:35:47,260 --> 00:35:49,460
Someone is framing a revolutionary cadre!

726
00:35:49,620 --> 00:35:50,460
Guo!

727
00:35:50,460 --> 00:35:52,340
- Here. Yes.
- Go report it to the police!

728
00:35:52,340 --> 00:35:53,260
You homewrecker.

729
00:35:53,260 --> 00:35:54,260
I'm telling you all.

730
00:35:54,260 --> 00:35:55,580
This is a political incident.

731
00:35:55,980 --> 00:35:56,820
Go home.

732
00:35:57,020 --> 00:35:58,700
I will track this down fully.

733
00:35:58,700 --> 00:35:59,540
Homewrecker.

734
00:36:00,620 --> 00:36:01,460
Go home.

735
00:36:02,060 --> 00:36:02,900
How are you guarding the door?

736
00:36:02,900 --> 00:36:04,220
You let just anyone come in.

737
00:36:04,220 --> 00:36:05,900
Close the door. Rehearsal.

738
00:36:07,860 --> 00:36:08,700
Whose kid is this?

739
00:36:10,060 --> 00:36:10,900
Auntie.

740
00:36:11,020 --> 00:36:11,860
Auntie.

741
00:36:12,300 --> 00:36:13,180
What?

742
00:36:13,180 --> 00:36:15,820
I was trying to charm Huang Zhengjing?

743
00:36:16,540 --> 00:36:18,940
Why would you?

744
00:36:18,940 --> 00:36:20,540
He'd need to be worth it first.

745
00:36:20,540 --> 00:36:21,380
Alright, alright.

746
00:36:21,660 --> 00:36:23,180
Enough, enough. Rehearsal.

747
00:36:23,580 --> 00:36:24,420
Go.

748
00:36:26,940 --> 00:36:27,780
Rehearsal.

749
00:36:28,380 --> 00:36:29,660
How'd you crash that badly?

750
00:36:29,660 --> 00:36:31,620
How'd it end up like this?

751
00:36:31,620 --> 00:36:34,060
That downhill was too steep.
I couldn't brake.

752
00:36:34,380 --> 00:36:35,220
I slammed into the mountain.

753
00:36:35,660 --> 00:36:36,860
I almost lost my life.

754
00:36:37,300 --> 00:36:38,180
Alright, alright.

755
00:36:38,180 --> 00:36:39,860
I never should've lent you the bike.

756
00:36:40,380 --> 00:36:41,220
You, you...

757
00:36:41,820 --> 00:36:43,660
This is the most valuable thing I own.

758
00:36:44,460 --> 00:36:46,020
Just wait till I save up some money.

759
00:36:46,020 --> 00:36:46,860
I...

760
00:36:47,180 --> 00:36:48,300
I'll buy you a new one.

761
00:36:48,540 --> 00:36:49,820
By the time you save enough,

762
00:36:50,060 --> 00:36:51,660
I won't live to see that day.

763
00:36:51,660 --> 00:36:52,540
Here, eat.

764
00:36:53,180 --> 00:36:54,180
Say thanks to your auntie.

765
00:36:57,620 --> 00:36:58,500
Where'd you wander off to?

766
00:36:59,460 --> 00:37:01,420
The county sent an inspection team.

767
00:37:01,900 --> 00:37:03,140
They took a few of us out,

768
00:37:03,140 --> 00:37:04,220
said it was for a little outing.

769
00:37:04,820 --> 00:37:05,860
Been a long time since I got out.

770
00:37:06,700 --> 00:37:07,980
Staying idle makes me restless.

771
00:37:08,540 --> 00:37:11,020
Can't you change that mule temper?

772
00:37:11,580 --> 00:37:13,340
Some things get into your bones.

773
00:37:14,020 --> 00:37:15,340
They don't change in this lifetime.

774
00:37:19,860 --> 00:37:20,700
Eat slowly.

775
00:37:23,460 --> 00:37:24,300
Your sister's kid?

776
00:37:25,220 --> 00:37:26,300
A mountain kid, sheep-herding type.

777
00:37:26,300 --> 00:37:27,380
A blank sheet of paper.

778
00:37:27,820 --> 00:37:29,100
Do you know who he is?

779
00:37:29,100 --> 00:37:31,220
A great scholar, very learned.

780
00:37:31,940 --> 00:37:33,740
He used to be the province's lead playwright.

781
00:37:34,420 --> 00:37:35,340
If you perform opera,

782
00:37:35,340 --> 00:37:37,300
and get to do one of his plays,

783
00:37:37,460 --> 00:37:38,580
you'll really become a star performer.

784
00:37:39,660 --> 00:37:41,260
Why tell the kid all that?

785
00:37:41,580 --> 00:37:42,540
You've scared the kid.

786
00:37:42,860 --> 00:37:44,220
Her eyes are glazed over.

787
00:37:47,380 --> 00:37:48,220
Oh, no.

788
00:37:48,340 --> 00:37:49,660
She's never had a steamed white-flour bun.

789
00:37:52,140 --> 00:37:53,060
She ate too fast and choked.

790
00:37:53,060 --> 00:37:53,900
Quick, quick, open your mouth.

791
00:37:53,900 --> 00:37:54,740
Get water, get water.

792
00:37:55,980 --> 00:37:57,100
Water, water, hurry!

793
00:37:57,100 --> 00:37:58,060
Use water to wash it down.

794
00:37:58,060 --> 00:37:58,900
Drink. Gulp it down.

795
00:37:58,940 --> 00:37:59,780
- Here.
- Easy, easy.

796
00:38:00,300 --> 00:38:01,140
Big gulps, big gulps.

797
00:38:15,820 --> 00:38:17,180
You ever taken a bus?

798
00:38:19,740 --> 00:38:20,580
What is it?

799
00:38:21,060 --> 00:38:21,900
Feeling sick?

800
00:38:22,380 --> 00:38:23,220
Carsick, right?

801
00:38:24,900 --> 00:38:25,980
Don't look to the side.

802
00:38:26,140 --> 00:38:27,180
Look straight ahead.

803
00:38:28,020 --> 00:38:29,220
Or just close your eyes.

804
00:38:29,220 --> 00:38:30,060
See if you can nap a bit.

805
00:38:42,540 --> 00:38:44,060
Those four buns were wasted.

806
00:38:59,420 --> 00:39:03,140
ظآزSocialism is good, so very goodظآز

807
00:39:03,140 --> 00:39:06,540
ظآزIn a socialist state, people stand tallظآز

808
00:39:06,540 --> 00:39:07,860
Pretty lively in the city, huh?

809
00:39:08,820 --> 00:39:12,620
ظآزThe imperialists ran off in defeatظآز

810
00:39:12,620 --> 00:39:15,460
ظآزAll our people stand united as oneظآز

811
00:39:15,460 --> 00:39:20,220
ظآزRaising a wave of socialist buildingظآز

812
00:39:20,220 --> 00:39:22,100
ظآزA wave of socialist buildingظآز

813
00:39:22,100 --> 00:39:25,820
ظآزThe Communist Party is goodظآز

814
00:39:25,820 --> 00:39:29,220
ظآزThe Party leads the people wellظآز

815
00:39:29,500 --> 00:39:31,460
ظآزIt means what it says and does itظآز

816
00:39:55,260 --> 00:39:56,100
Here we are.

817
00:39:58,060 --> 00:40:01,340
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

818
00:40:01,340 --> 00:40:03,580
This is where your uncle works.

819
00:40:03,580 --> 00:40:04,860
From now on, this is your home.

820
00:40:05,700 --> 00:40:06,940
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)
Master Hu, who's this?

821
00:40:07,460 --> 00:40:08,300
My niece.

822
00:40:08,420 --> 00:40:09,260
Going out?

823
00:40:10,460 --> 00:40:11,580
Look how good my move is.

824
00:40:11,580 --> 00:40:13,060
No backing out now.

825
00:40:14,220 --> 00:40:15,780
Just don't take your move back.

826
00:40:18,420 --> 00:40:19,260
This old Master Gou...

827
00:40:19,260 --> 00:40:20,820
Why slam the piece down so hard?

828
00:40:21,220 --> 00:40:22,060
You scared the kid.

829
00:40:22,380 --> 00:40:23,340
Whose kid is this?

830
00:40:23,620 --> 00:40:24,460
My niece.

831
00:40:24,980 --> 00:40:25,860
Call him Master Gou.

832
00:40:26,620 --> 00:40:27,860
Not Gou like a guard dog.

833
00:40:27,860 --> 00:40:29,380
Gou as in just getting by.

834
00:40:29,900 --> 00:40:31,100
I'm basically a guard dog.

835
00:40:31,380 --> 00:40:32,420
Right, right, right.

836
00:40:32,820 --> 00:40:33,820
And this is Master Qiu.

837
00:40:33,820 --> 00:40:36,180
Be sweet to him, you'll have meat to eat.

838
00:40:36,180 --> 00:40:37,020
He handles the meals.

839
00:40:37,220 --> 00:40:38,660
I'd like some meat too.

840
00:40:38,660 --> 00:40:40,300
Be glad you get enough to eat.

841
00:40:40,900 --> 00:40:41,740
A kid from the mountains.

842
00:40:41,820 --> 00:40:43,300
Brought her back to see the world.

843
00:40:43,820 --> 00:40:45,260
What is there to see around here?

844
00:40:45,580 --> 00:40:46,420
Ghosts?

845
00:40:46,860 --> 00:40:47,700
Move. Move. Move.

846
00:40:48,060 --> 00:40:49,060
Move. Move. Move.

847
00:40:49,060 --> 00:40:49,940
He Dachui, what happened?

848
00:40:49,940 --> 00:40:50,780
It's life-concerning.

849
00:40:51,460 --> 00:40:52,300
What happened? Who is it?

850
00:40:57,340 --> 00:40:58,180
Move. Move!

851
00:40:58,380 --> 00:40:59,220
What happened, Director Huang?

852
00:41:01,180 --> 00:41:02,060
What happened?

853
00:41:02,060 --> 00:41:03,540
Who was it? I didn't see clearly.

854
00:41:03,700 --> 00:41:04,620
Me, neither.

855
00:41:08,780 --> 00:41:10,220
Master Hu, what happened to your leg?

856
00:41:10,580 --> 00:41:11,740
I'm fine. I took a fall.

857
00:41:12,100 --> 00:41:12,940
Little beggar.

858
00:41:14,260 --> 00:41:15,100
Go.

859
00:41:15,580 --> 00:41:16,740
Where'd this little beggar come from?

860
00:41:17,420 --> 00:41:18,260
What are you saying?

861
00:41:20,220 --> 00:41:21,060
Sanyuan.

862
00:41:21,060 --> 00:41:21,900
Come here.

863
00:41:22,460 --> 00:41:23,300
Come have a drink.

864
00:41:23,300 --> 00:41:25,380
We caught a snake in the yard.

865
00:41:25,380 --> 00:41:26,220
Tastes amazing.

866
00:41:26,220 --> 00:41:27,100
Come.

867
00:41:27,100 --> 00:41:28,100
Don't let it upset your stomach.

868
00:41:28,460 --> 00:41:29,500
No, I won't drink.

869
00:41:29,500 --> 00:41:30,340
You drink. Go ahead.

870
00:41:30,340 --> 00:41:31,180
Make it tasty, okay?

871
00:41:31,260 --> 00:41:32,100
Sure, no problem.

872
00:41:32,860 --> 00:41:33,700
Get in.

873
00:41:33,700 --> 00:41:34,780
Come on, come on.

874
00:41:34,780 --> 00:41:35,620
Eat, eat.

875
00:41:38,860 --> 00:41:39,700
It's good.

876
00:41:42,860 --> 00:41:43,700
You're back.

877
00:41:46,020 --> 00:41:47,060
What happened with the troupe?

878
00:41:48,820 --> 00:41:51,020
Huang Zhengjing's wife drank pesticide.

879
00:41:51,020 --> 00:41:52,020
They were rushed to the hospital.

880
00:41:52,580 --> 00:41:53,660
Huang Zhengjing's wife?

881
00:41:53,940 --> 00:41:54,860
Why drank pesticide?

882
00:41:57,020 --> 00:41:59,060
No idea who did something so vile.

883
00:41:59,260 --> 00:42:01,100
Someone sent her an anonymous letter.

884
00:42:01,340 --> 00:42:03,740
It said the troupe's leading actress

885
00:42:04,180 --> 00:42:05,260
was charming Huang Zhengjing.

886
00:42:06,220 --> 00:42:07,820
And his wife was such a fool.

887
00:42:08,260 --> 00:42:09,900
She came to settle the score with me.

888
00:42:10,220 --> 00:42:11,660
She caused a scene in the rehearsal hall.

889
00:42:11,940 --> 00:42:14,220
Huang Zhengjing felt humiliated,

890
00:42:14,220 --> 00:42:15,100
so he sent her back.

891
00:42:15,100 --> 00:42:16,540
But in a fit of anger, she drank pesticide.

892
00:42:19,820 --> 00:42:21,660
You were charming Huang Zhengjing?

893
00:42:22,620 --> 00:42:23,540
It's just a rumor.

894
00:42:23,540 --> 00:42:25,020
They're trying to smear my name.

895
00:42:26,620 --> 00:42:28,220
Who wrote that anonymous letter?

896
00:42:29,100 --> 00:42:30,180
The Head of Security Section...

897
00:42:30,820 --> 00:42:31,660
Who?

898
00:42:31,900 --> 00:42:32,740
He's incapable.

899
00:42:33,020 --> 00:42:35,060
He investigated all day and got nowhere.

900
00:42:35,620 --> 00:42:37,500
Just say it all in one go.

901
00:42:39,460 --> 00:42:40,900
Who do you think did it?

902
00:42:41,100 --> 00:42:42,140
Whoever it was,

903
00:42:42,980 --> 00:42:45,380
they sure fixed Huang Zhengjing.

904
00:42:46,420 --> 00:42:48,100
Let's see if he still spends all day

905
00:42:48,260 --> 00:42:49,780
chatting up women now.

906
00:42:51,300 --> 00:42:52,580
What happened to your leg?

907
00:42:52,940 --> 00:42:54,060
I took a spill off my bike.

908
00:42:54,060 --> 00:42:56,060
I'm fine, just scrapes. No bones hurt.

909
00:42:56,300 --> 00:42:58,220
You're always so careless.

910
00:42:58,220 --> 00:42:59,860
You get hurt doing anything.

911
00:42:59,860 --> 00:43:01,300
Watch your behavior. The kid's here.

912
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

913
00:43:09,280 --> 00:43:10,250
There cannot be two tigers

914
00:43:10,250 --> 00:43:11,700
on one mountain.

915
00:43:12,060 --> 00:43:13,700
Aunt Hua is the troupe's star performer.

916
00:43:13,700 --> 00:43:15,060
She'll be your teacher someday.

917
00:43:15,060 --> 00:43:16,150
Where are you from?

918
00:43:16,360 --> 00:43:17,420
You're here for the troupe too?

919
00:43:20,190 --> 00:43:21,060
Open wider.

920
00:43:21,670 --> 00:43:22,700
You two are really something.

921
00:43:22,700 --> 00:43:24,070
Having a mute kid perform opera?

922
00:43:24,320 --> 00:43:26,270
The anonymous letter caused trouble.

923
00:43:26,520 --> 00:43:27,880
You and Hua Caixiang won't join

924
00:43:28,130 --> 00:43:29,820
the trainee recruitment work.

925
00:43:30,220 --> 00:43:31,210
In this situation,

926
00:43:31,210 --> 00:43:32,360
let's hurry and figure this out.

927
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
ظآزWhen I woke up and turned backظآز

928
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
ظآزI wasn't sure where to goظآز

929
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
ظآزWe met and brushed pastظآز

930
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
ظآزYour shadow drifted out of sightظآز

931
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
ظآزThe stove fire blazed in my dreamظآز

932
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
ظآزLit up the tracks of pearly tearsظآز

933
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
ظآزIn my dream, water sleeves flewظآز

934
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
ظآزHiding a lifetime of loveظآز

935
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
ظآزThe Qinling Mountains
crossed the stageظآز

936
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
ظآزSpring water brewed strong wineظآز

937
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
ظآزSheep moved through the valleyظآز

938
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
ظآزIt felt like a promise
from another lifeظآز

939
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
ظآزWhen I woke up and turned backظآز

940
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
ظآزI wasn't sure where to goظآز

941
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
ظآزIf I chose again, I'd still roamظآز

942
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
ظآزAll over this sunlit plateauظآز

943
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
ظآزThe dream ends; the curtain fallsظآز

944
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
ظآزMoonlight washes off this stage makeupظآز

945
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
ظآزThe one in the mirror wears gray hairظآز

946
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
ظآزAlready sang all my joy and sorrowظآز

947
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
ظآزAlready shouted across Qinchuan Plainظآز
